    "reasoning": "To design this FSM, we must follow the state transitions described in the problem statement. The FSM needs to detect the pattern 1101, then shift in 4 more bits, wait for counting to complete, and notify the user. We define states for detecting the pattern, shifting, counting, and waiting for acknowledgment. Using 'localparam' for states ensures clarity. The sequential logic uses posedge clk for state transitions and reset. The FSM transitions through states as per the requirement: INIT -> DETECT -> SHIFT -> COUNT -> DONE -> ACK -> INIT. The output signals are driven based on current state. Care must be taken to properly handle state transitions and outputs. The use of 'always @(*)' for combinational logic is important. To avoid syntax errors, ensure all signals are declared correctly as 'logic', and use appropriate bit ordering.",
    "module": "module TopModule (\n    input clk,\n    input reset,\n    input data,\n    input done_counting,\n    input ack,\n    output reg shift_ena,\n    output reg counting,\n    output reg done\n);\n\n    // Define states\n    localparam INIT         = 3'd0;\n    localparam DETECT       = 3'd1;\n    localparam SHIFT        = 3'd2;\n    localparam COUNT        = 3'd3;\n    localparam DONE         = 3'd4;\n    localparam ACK          = 3'd5;\n\n    // State register\n    logic [2:0] state;\n    logic [2:0] next_state;\n\n    // Shift register for pattern detection\n    logic [3:0] shift_reg;\n\n    // Sequential logic for state\n    always @(posedge clk) begin\n        if (reset)\n            state <= INIT;\n        else\n            state <= next_state;\n    end\n\n    // Next state logic\n    always @(*) begin\n        case (state)\n            INIT: begin\n                if ((shift_reg == 4'b1101))\n                    next_state = DETECT;\n                else\n                    next_state = INIT;\n            end\n            DETECT: next_state = SHIFT;\n            SHIFT: next_state = COUNT;\n            COUNT: begin\n                if (done_counting)\n                    next_state = DONE;\n                else\n                    next_state = COUNT;\n            end\n            DONE: begin\n                if (ack)\n                    next_state = INIT;\n                else\n                    next_state = DONE;\n            end\n            ACK: next_state = INIT;\n            default: next_state = INIT;\n        endcase\n    end\n\n    // Output logic\n    always @(*) begin\n        shift_ena = 1'b0;\n        counting = 1'b0;\n        done = 1'b0;\n        \n        case (state)\n            SHIFT: shift_ena = 1'b1;\n            COUNT: counting = 1'b1;\n            DONE: done = 1'b1;\n        endcase\n    end\n\nendmodule"
}
