hift_ena = stats1.errors_shift_ena+1\'b1; \n\t\tend\n\t\tif (counting_ref !== ( counting_ref ^ counting_dut ^ counting_ref ))\n\t\tbegin \n\t\t\tif (stats1.errors_counting == 0) stats1.errortime_counting = $time;\n\t\t\tstats1.errors_counting = stats1.errors_counting+1\'b1; \n\t\tend\n\t\tif (done_ref !== ( done_ref ^ done_dut ^ done_ref ))\n\t\tbegin \n\t\t\tif (stats1.errors_done == 0) stats1.errortime_done = $time;\n\t\t\tstats1.errors_done = stats1.errors_done+1\'b1; \n\t\tend\n\n\tend\n\n\t// add timeout after 100K cycles\n\tinitial begin\n\t\t#1000000\n\t\t$display("TIMEOUT");\n\t\t$finish();\n\tend\n\nendmodule\n</generated_tb>\n<sim_failed_log>\n{\n    "stdout": "VCD info: dumpfile wave.vcd opened for output.\\nFIRST MISMATCH AT TIME 90:\\nInput signals: clk=0 reset=0 data=x done_counting=x ack=x\\nOutput signals: shift_ena=0 counting=0 done=0\\nExpected signals: shift_ena=1 counting=0 done=0\\nHint: Your FSM didn\'t pass the sample timing diagram posted with the problem statement. Perhaps try debugging that?\\n./output_t22c_qwen3coder30b_shard4_0/VERILOG_EVAL_V2_Prob151_review2015_fsm/tb.sv:74: $finish called at 25346 (1ps)\\nHint: Output \'shift_ena\' has 208 mismatches. First mismatch occurred at time 90.\\nHint: Output \'counting\' has 336 mismatches. First mismatch occurred at time 110.\\nHint: Output \'done\' has 196 mismatches. First mismatch occurred at time 6850.\\nHint: Total mismatched samples is 456 out of 5069 samples\\n\\nSimulation finished at 25346 ps\\nMismatches: 456 in 5069 samples\\nSIMULATION FAILED - 456 MISMATCHES DETECTED, FIRST AT TIME 90\\n",\n    "stderr": ""\n}\n</sim_failed_log>\n\n[Hints]:\nFor implementing kmap (Karnaugh map), you need to think and solve mismatches step by step.\nFind the inputs corresponding to mismatch in sim_failed_log, and set the output to correct value while maintaining other outputs.\n')]), ChatMessage(role=<MessageRole.ASSISTANT: 'assistant'>, additional_kwargs={}, blocks=[TextBlock(block_type='text', t